rib /rɪb/

(ribs) 

1. N-COUNT Your ribs are the 12 pairs of curved bones that surround your chest. 肋骨 

例： Her heart was thumping against her ribs. 当时她的心挨着她的肋骨砰砰直跳。 

2. N-COUNT A rib of meat such as beef or pork is a piece that has been cut to include one of the animal's ribs. 排骨 

例： ...a rib of beef. …一块牛小排。 

例： ...pork ribs. …猪排骨。 

3. N a part or element similar in function or appearance to a rib, esp a structural or supporting member or a raised strip or ridge 

4. V to furnish or support with a rib or ribs 装肋状物于; 用肋状物支撑 

5. V to tease or ridicule 戏弄; 嘲笑 

6. N a joke or hoax 玩笑; 恶作剧

